  "prompt": "Why when I urinate does my urine sometimes come out in two directions simultaneously?",
  "response": "Urine can sometimes flow in two directions simultaneously due to a variety of factors:\n\n1. **Urethral Stricture**: A narrowing of the urethra can cause urine to divert in different directions.\n   \n2. **Prostate Issues**: For men, an enlarged prostate can affect urine flow and lead to splitting.\n\n3. **Pelvic Floor Dysfunction**: Muscular issues can impact how urine is expelled.\n\n4. **Anatomical Variations**: Some people may have unique anatomical variations in their urinary system.\n\n5. **Positioning**: The way you position yourself while urinating can also influence urine direction.\n\nIf this occurs frequently or is accompanied by pain, changes in urination patterns, or other concerning symptoms, it's best to consult a healthcare professional for a proper evaluation and guidance.",
